reviewText: If you remember Electric Light Orchestra from the 1970's and 1980's, this is the LIVE, ON-STAGE reunion in Hyde Park, England. This is a live concert, with full orchestra on stage. No special effects, no 64 track mixing boards and over dubs. This is ELO playing all the songs that made them famous (and a few others). THEY SOUND GREAT!  GREAT LIVE PERFORMANCE YOU CAN'T MISS IF YOU LIKED ELO! Show this to your kids so that they know what a REAL musical performance looks and sounds like.
Don't order the UK version.  You may not receive it while your young enough to enjoy it.

If you could only listen to one classic rock concert, this is the one to watch and listen. Jeff Lynne, of course, is the maestro of rock and just listening to this, even though it's live, is like listening to an ELO album. I had most of this stuff on vinyl back in the day and it's a great  trip down memory lane.
Was concerned about ordering the UK version (in order to get Roll Over Beethoven) but it plays just fine on my Playstation3.
